article.description: Brandon Clarke had 18 points and nine rebounds and San Jose State tied a program record with 30 assists in a 109-70 win over Life Pacific on Saturday.
article.headline: San Jose State beats Life Pacific 109-70
article.linkText: San Jose State beats Life Pacific 109-70
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Brandon Clarke had 18 points and nine rebounds and San Jose State tied a program record with 30 assists in a 109-70 win over Life Pacific on Saturday. Cody Schwartz added 17 points for the Spartans (5-4), who had their second 100-point game in a season for the first time since 1970-71. San Jose State was 13 of 25 from 3-point range and 39 of 71 overall from the field. Ryan Welage had 14 points, Gary Williams Jr. and Jaycee Hillsman scored 11 each and Terrell Brown 10. The NCCAA-member Warriors shot nearly as well (13 of 28) as the Spartans from 3-point range. But San Jose State had 17 more overall attempts from the field thanks to a 48-18 edge in rebounding, including 19-2 on the offensive glass. Ramez Michail and Mark Eden had 15 points each and Edgardo Campos added 12 for Life Pacific.
